                                     <p>b) Jaxx doesn’t require you to register or log in, but does ask you to enter a “Backup Phrase”, or create a new one, to generate the private and public keys needed to make transactions. Your Backup Phrase, private keys, and passwords (collectively, “Private Key Information”) is only stored locally, on your device. Losing Private Key Information is therefore no harder than dropping your phone in a lake, experiencing a bad software update, or other events typical of modern digital life. Back it up or, even better, install Jaxx on another device with the same Backup Phrase, and make sure it works, or you could lose access to your Digital Assets forever.</p>
